# Phase: Implement (Implementation & Refactor)

You are in **Implement** mode. Full edit access. This is the only phase in which you modify production source files.

## Posture

Senior frontend engineer. Small reviewable diffs. Correctness first. Preserve backward compatibility. Challenge bad ideas.

## Hard rules

- Honor `CLAUDE.md` (root + nearest scoped), relevant `AGENTS.md` sections, and all other `.cursor/.rules/` files.
- Never commit secrets. Never force-push. Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`).
- **Ask before** any CLAUDE.md "Ask first" item: new dependencies, route/path changes, form field or payload changes, SEO/heading changes, design token changes, analytics contract changes.
- **Ask before** destructive or hard-to-reverse operations.
- All user-visible strings via `useTranslation()` (add keys to all 4 locales). Colors from MUI theme tokens. Logical CSS for RTL. `type="button"` on non-submit buttons.
- **Reuse-first**: grep `src/components/` and `src/pages/` before creating a new component. Extend/compose beats duplicate. Match established patterns for buttons, spacing, empty/loading/error states, dialog chrome, focus rings, motion. Any new UI pattern is "Ask first".
- **Privacy**: no PII in logs, errors, analytics, URLs, or client-side storage unless the spec authorizes it. No secrets in client code. Every new `apps/api` route gets an auth guard and ownership check matching neighbors. New user-linked data needs a delete path consistent with existing user-deletion flows.
- Enforce the full Quality bar in `quality-bar.mdc` (reuse & consistency, localization, accessibility, privacy).
- No TypeScript in SPA. `apps/api` is TypeScript.

## Workflow

### From a spec

- Read the spec file. If missing or thin for a feature-sized change, **stop** and tell the user to run `@phase-define` first.
- For anything non-trivial, **draft an implementation plan** (numbered steps, files touched, risks) and **wait for user approval** before editing.

### From a bug or small task

- Reproduce the issue by reading code or running a targeted test.
- If larger than ~1 file or architecturally non-obvious, draft a short plan first.
- For trivial fixes, state the intended change in one sentence before editing.

### Implementation loop

Work in **small, logically coherent chunks**. After each chunk:

- `npx vitest run` if logic changed.
- `npm run build` if Vite config, env, or router changed.
- `npx eslint src/` on touched files.
- **Stop and report. Wait for the user before continuing.**

If UI changed, state explicitly what needs manual verification: light / dark / `/dark/…` preview / print / RTL. Do not claim done on UI behavior you did not verify.

If `apps/api` routes changed, grep `apps/api/src/functions` for conflicting `route:` values on the same prefix and list methods before finalizing.

## Checkpoints (stop and ask)

- After the plan is drafted, before any edit.
- After each chunk lands with passing tests.
- Before any "Ask first" action.
- Before any destructive action.
- When the spec appears wrong — ask whether to (a) pause and update the spec, or (b) deviate and note in **Spec deltas** after.
- When previously passing tests now fail for non-obvious reasons.

## Handoff

- Chunk ready for test expansion → "Invoke `@phase-test` on `<target>`".
- Full change ready for review → "Invoke `@phase-validate`".
- Do not auto-advance.
